# Mouse open-drain equivalence (AGENT.md §6, README Tier 2). MousePM.v's MouseP has
# bidirectional open-drain `inout msclk, msdat`; our gate splits each into a *_oe drive + a
# resolved-value input. mouse_shim.v wraps BOTH into one interface (a free external read +
# the resolved line as the observable). Driven by Yosys_equiv.run_proof. Placeholders (named
# WITHOUT braces here — substitution is blind and would splice into this comment):
#   rtl        MousePM.v          shims  mouse_shim.v        ours/gate  our emitted gate
#   gold_shim/ours_shim  the two wrappers
#   gold_renames/ours_renames  per-wrapper cd/rename block stripping the g. instance prefix
read_verilog {rtl}
read_verilog {shims}
read_verilog {ours}
hierarchy -check
proc
flatten {gold_shim}
flatten {ours_shim}
# lower the open-drain inout to plain logic: convert ALL tristate (incl. the inout-port
# drivers) to enable-gated logic, drop tribuf's "no two drivers" assertion (open-drain
# legally has many low drivers), and tie the both-released float to 1 (the pad pull-up) —
# together exactly `line = oe ? 0 : ext` on both sides
tribuf -formal
chformal -remove
setundef -one
# strip the g. instance prefix the flatten added, pairing the wrapped FFs to the RTL names
{gold_renames}
{ours_renames}
memory
opt
equiv_make {gold_shim} {ours_shim} equiv
hierarchy -top equiv
opt -full
equiv_simple
equiv_induct
equiv_status -assert
